-- Polish Stocks: Drugmaker Krka, Builder PBG Active in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-04-11T15:50:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/polish-stocks-drugmaker-krka-builder-pbg-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  climbed 1.2
percent to 2,251.89 at the close in Warsaw.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Krka Group d.d.  (KRK PW), gained as Slovenia’s biggest
pharmaceutical company made its debut on the Warsaw Stock
Exchange today. The shares closed at 210 zloty, compared with a
reference price set by the bourse at 202.1 zloty. The company’s
stock in Ljubljana rose 1.2 percent to 49 euros.  PBG SA (PBG)  , Poland’s third-largest construction
company rose 0.8 percent to 33.67 zloty after falling to as low
as 31 zloty as it said it expects negative operating cash flow
this quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
